body:
I have made the changes based on your suggestions.

Was wondering if we wanted to have some sort of way of registering for notification of a watch being removed, or if we just do it via the CuratorListener?

Currently you need to register a CuratorListener and then check

if(event.getType() == CuratorEventType.WATCHED && event.getWatchedVent().getType() == EventType.DataWatchRemoved)
{
}

(or EventType.ChildWatchRemoved).

Maybe a new type of listener interface? Or is this overkill?
